    How does petite point differ from needlepoint?
    With roots in ancient history, needlepoint has evolved over time and is today often associated with decor items such as pillows and upholstery, as well as wall art. Petit point, on the other hand, is a type of needlepoint that utilises smaller stitches and finer canvas to achieve more detailed and subtle designs.

    What is the history of petite point?
    The art of the Petit Point originated at the French court, where the women mostly embroidered coarser tapestries. As the generations and epochs changed, the stitches became finer and finer, the threads thinner and thinner and the colors more sophisticated.

    How do you choose a petite point design?
    Picking a Pattern for Petit Point

    Petit point pretty much uses the same patterns as cross stitch. Any petit point pattern can be easily cross stitched. However, when converting a cross stitch pattern to petit point you want to avoid patterns that have lots of 1/4 and 3/4 stitches, and patterns with lots of backstitch.    3 Jul 2020
